article_metadata.description: Fewer than half as many people will enroll in exchange plans in 2016 as experts projected when the law passed six years ago. Risk pools appear that they will once again be dominated by people earning less than twice the poverty level who tend to be older and less healthy than anticipated.
article_metadata.author: The Apothecary
